LIMITED EDITION SS25 | Marking the second anniversary of Art in Progress, we celebrate a unique fusion of creative expression: fashion and art converge in a dreamlike, immersive show. Massimo Dutti transforms its iconic PCG96 store into a vibrant runway where fashion, art, and craftsmanship intertwine, creating an atmosphere of creative emergence.
 
By breaking down traditional barriers between creative disciplines, this initiative fosters a renewed dialogue between fashion, art, and the public, uniting practices and perspectives in a shared celebration of creation.
 
Artists:
 
@armandomesias : Ostinato, 2023.
Oil, spray paint, charcoal, pen, Totomoxtle ash, pigment, and acrylic on patchwork of cotton and denim.
 
@Laurentmartinlobamboo: Cosmic Brother, 2014-2016.
Weather beaten bamboo, steel rings and hooks, ceramic balls.
 
@Gabrielescamez: Arc 180 Square Lamps, 2024.
Off white cotton, brown leather.
 
@Ombredansleau: Feminae, Morbid num II.
Stoneware clay with grog fired at high temperature.
 
@Antoniogonzalez.me: Work2.
Oil on Canvas.
 
@Ombredansleau: The Snail, 2020.
Beige stoneware clay with grog fired at high temperature in wood kiln.
 
Galleries:
 
@Vasto_gallery
@Alzueta_gallery
 
